{"id":51670,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jochen_Rindt","text":"Karl Jochen Rindt (born April 18 1942 in Mainz, Germany \u2013 died September 5 1970 in Monza) was a German racing driver who represented Austria during his career. In 1970, he won the Formula One World Drivers' Championship, but died in a crash in Monza. He was the only driver to win the championship after he died.\nIn 1965 he won the 24 Hours of Le Mans race.","categories":[],"infobox_types":["Le Mans driver"],"annotations":[{"uri":"April_18","surface_form":"April 18","offset":24},{"uri":"1942","surface_form":"1942","offset":33},{"uri":"Mainz","surface_form":"Mainz","offset":41},{"uri":"Germany","surface_form":"Germany","offset":48},{"uri":"September_5","surface_form":"September 5","offset":63},{"uri":"1970","surface_form":"1970","offset":75},{"uri":"Monza","surface_form":"Monza","offset":83},{"uri":"Germany","surface_form":"German","offset":96},{"uri":"Austria","surface_form":"Austria","offset":133},{"uri":"1970","surface_form":"1970","offset":163},{"uri":"Formula_One","surface_form":"Formula One","offset":180},{"uri":"Accident","surface_form":"crash","offset":235},{"uri":"Monza","surface_form":"Monza","offset":244},{"uri":"24_Hours_of_Le_Mans","surface_form":"24 Hours of Le Mans","offset":332}]}